headline: Solutions Architect at CGI
jobDescription2:
Design and development of the ARGOS control software. The ARGOS project  equips the Large Binocular Telescope with a laser guide star and wavefront sensing facility. ARGOS uses six pulsed lasers to generate artificial guide stars to correct the ground layer turbulence above each of the LBT mirrors.

Design, development, and commissioning of the real time system which monitors and compensates the telescope vibrations. The real time acquisition system collects data from 48 accelerometers installed all over the telescope and broadcasts this data to the different subsystems using a multicast protocol.

Design, development and documentation of the Instrument control Interface (IIF) for the Large Binocular Telescope (LBT) located in Arizona.
LBT is a 2x8.4 mts binocular telescope, an international collaboration, with partners from the United States, Italy, and Germany. 
IIF is the software interface which allows the instrument software to communicate with the Telescope Control System (TCS) and its different subsystems. More information in www.lbto.org.

Developing the Daemon for the Infrared Test Camera Interface for LBT (Dirti), which is used during commissioning campaigns.
